<-------------Values and Principles of agility - Quiz 1---------------->

Q1. Which Agile value is being violated?
Answer: b) Customer Collaboration over Contract Negotiation
The team is relying on the contract and taking sign-offs rather than actively collaborating with the customer. Agile values customer collaboration over strictly following contract terms.

Q2. Which represents the Primary Measure of Progress?
Answer: d) Registration feature which was released to customer's demo
As per the Agile Manifesto, working software is the primary measure of progress. A feature released to the customer's demo is working software, unlike documentation, architecture, or reviewed code which are intermediate artifacts.

<---------------Prioritization of User Stories - Quiz 1----------------->

Q1. The customer categorizes all the user stories in the product backlog as very important. The scrum master proposes to add a few more teams as and when required to develop the user stories in parallel.
Answer: b) False

Q2. The customer feels a particular story needs to be developed immediately. However, the development team has concerns on doing it. The Scrum master stops from mentioning it to the customer.
Answer: b) False

Q3. For a set of user stories, the development team feels that they need to scale up and have concerns on developing it immediately. They place these stories under "High" risk items.
Answer: a) True

Q4. The customer mentions about a feature that they have in mind, but may not have budget in this quarter to have it developed. The Development team puts this under "Wont have" category.
Answer: a) True

Q5. The Scrum master forces the team to pick up the story despite the development team's technical incapability.
Answer: b) False

