<-------------Produce Working Software - Quiz 1-------------->

Q1. One of the Scrum teams have created HLD and LLD documents and brought it for sprint review.
Answer:

a) HLD and LLD documents do not represent working increments.
c) A skeleton code / wireframes to prove the design represents a working increment.


Q2. The sprint burndown chart shows 240 hours pending across 9 days and 0 hours on the 10th day.
Answer: a) The team members have not updated their work regularly and have updated it on the last day

Q3. What action should the scrum master take if team members do not update task efforts?
Answer: a) Sensitize and provide mild penalties, check the status before standup meeting

<--------------------Daily Scrum Meeting - Quiz 1--------------------->
Q1. What could be the reasons for the team member absenting himself from the daily standup meeting?
Answer:
a) He has not completed the committed work and hence has nothing to say in the standup meeting
b) He has committed for a huge task(>12 hrs) and hence his task is in pending state.
c) He is struggling with the task committed and is not confident of saying it in front of the team.
d) He is worried that his performance appraisal would be affected if he says his tasks are not complete.


Q2. Choose the statements which align to the guidelines of a standup meeting.
Answer:
f) Each team member provides answers to the three questions and others listen.

<--------------------Product Backlog Grooming - Quiz 1--------------->

Q1. A scrum team raises an issue that they do not have enough "produce time" in the sprint and that the planning is taking a lot of time. What could be going wrong here?
Answer: 
a) The team is not sprinting ahead. They may be grooming stories during sprint planning
b) PO is not providing timely response to user stories and hence sprint planning is taking long
c) The product backlog grooming exercise is not happening properly
